      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;1-installation&#34;&gt;1 Installation&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;11-installation-for-python-environment&#34;&gt;1.1 Installation for python environment&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To install &lt;code&gt;nvcc&lt;/code&gt; inside a Python virtual environment, conda is all you need. It lets you pick the exact CUDA version for each env, so you never clash with system-wide installs. Please follow the steps below to install &lt;code&gt;nvcc&lt;/code&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Search for all available &lt;code&gt;nvcc&lt;/code&gt; version&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
